# Junk-directory guard rules
# Scopes the source behind default-excluding well-known junk directories
# (.terraform, node_modules, .zig-cache, zig-out, .venv, __pycache__, target,
# dist) from implicit directory-glob expansion, plus the loud per-rule oversize
# warning: the junk-dir set + explicit-reinclude helper + oversize thresholds
# (junk.go), and the walkAndEmit skip + the two warn call sites (resolver.go).
# Changes to any of these should trigger the cx-junk-dirs E2E scenario, which
# runs `cx generate` over a project with a .terraform/ blob and asserts the junk
# is skipped implicitly but re-included by an explicit rule.
# Paths are relative to the cx repo root.

pkg/context/junk.go
pkg/context/resolver.go
tests/e2e/scenarios_junk_dirs.go
